<br>
I started reclaiming ms2 until i had enough mana to cast, finished, summoned aoe trods, then started to meditate.  Normally I would have kept reclaiming pets until I was FM again, but some guildies were going afk for a few and Kei was on, so I just decided to med through.<br>
<br>
Then the train hit.  I had at least 10 mobs on me in the blink of an eye, had the slightest moment to call out clerics camp, and then took a dirt nap.  <br>
<br>
Our monk was still in camp... and everyone was where they were supposed to be.  So it couldnt have been from a bad pull.  Nothing had previously escaped our group and came back later.  It was a clean raid up until that very moment.  Nobody was grav fluxed, nobody ever touched the wall. Etc....<br>
<br>
But every single one of those mobs were decidely out to plant me 6 feet under.  I was Numero Uno on the hate list....literally.<br>
<br>
I hadn't popped a pet the whole raid.  I was and am always very careful about keeping aggro on the MT.  So what happened?  My only assumption is that the Monster Summoning Gods granted me an ashbone drake, it physically clipped through the 2nd floor, and then brought heaven and earth....and inevitably hell.<br>
<br>
So if this indeed was the case what happened to pets being indifferent to mobs?  <br>
<br>
thoughts? <p>Deviction Xue <br>
lvl 57 Mage<br>
